    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1456"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1456">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 612.002/90.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Canada</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 5, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At request Spanish Ambassador, use good offices with Carranza to facilitate safe
                    arrival at Mexico City of goods stated by Ambassador to be valued at 10,000,000
                    pesos belonging to Spanish, French and English importers and in transit from
                    Vera Cruz concerning which fears for safety are entertained because of
                    discontinued railway operations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
